+/* MP6 native port -- M4c ("Message Dir Over" crash fix, docs/NO_LEAK_POLICY.md-
+ * adjacent menus milestone). HuWinMesSet/HuWinInsertMesSet's "is messNum a
+ * real pointer, or a packed dir<<16|num value?" check was `messNum &
+ * 0x80000000` -- reliable on real hardware, where EVERY live pointer
+ * (static .bss/.data OR heap) unconditionally starts at MEM1's
+ * 0x80000000 base. This port's low-4GB game arena (platform/os/arena.c)
+ * deliberately starts at 0x80000000 too, for this exact reason (see that
+ * file's own header comment) -- so HEAP pointers still satisfy the
+ * check -- but the executable's own fixed, non-ASLR image base
+ * (tools/build.py's IMAGE_BASE=0x10000000) does NOT, so a STATIC/GLOBAL
+ * (.bss/.data) buffer address passed this way has bit 31 CLEAR and gets
+ * misclassified as a small packed dir/num value instead. Confirmed by
+ * direct reproduction: REL/fileseldll/filesel.c's fn_1_36C4 passes
+ * `(u32)p->unk_60` (the address of a static per-save-slot text buffer,
+ * `lbl_1_bss_D8[]`, living in the image's low .bss -- around 0x10xxxxxx,
+ * not 0x80000000+) to HuWinInsertMesSet; the low bit pattern of THAT
+ * address decodes as a huge, bogus "directory" once right-shifted 16,
+ * printing "Error: Message Dir Over" and then (since neither original
+ * error path actually returns) chasing a wild offset computed from it --
+ * a real access violation, resolved via dbghelp to a crash inside
+ * mp6_be32, called from HuWinMesDataPtrGet, called from
+ * HuWinInsertMesSet's own HuWinMesPtrGet call, reading address
+ * 0xB0950670 (neither a valid heap nor image address). Real dir/num
+ * encodings are always tiny (dir<<16|num; the largest dir this whole
+ * codebase ever uses is under 0x100) -- comfortably below EVERY real
+ * pointer this port ever produces, whether image-based (0x10000000+) or
+ * arena-based (0x80000000+/0x90000000+/0xA0000000+/0xB0000000+) -- so a
+ * generous, safely-in-between threshold replaces the bit-31 check with
+ * one that is still correct for real hardware's own address range AND
+ * this port's. */
+#define MP6_MESSNUM_ENCODED_MAX 0x01000000u
+
